	"readme": "# Tailwind PostCSS Spacing\n\nPostCSS plugin that converts `px`/`rem` values to `calc(var(--spacing) * n)` expressions. Perfect for scalable design systems.\n\n## Features\n\n- üîÑ Converts `px`/`rem` to `calc(var(--spacing) * n)`\n- üéØ Configurable base unit (default: 4px)\n- üõ°Ô∏è Preserves hairline borders (‚â§1px)\n- üìê Handles multiple values\n- ‚öôÔ∏è Property filtering support\n- üì¶ Universal: ES Module, CommonJS & UMD builds included\n\n## Installation\n\n```bash\nnpm install tailwind-postcss-spacing --save-dev\n```\n\n## Usage\n\n```javascript\n// postcss.config.js\nimport tailwindPostcssSpacing from 'tailwind-postcss-spacing'\n\nexport default {\n  plugins: [tailwindPostcssSpacing()]\n}\n```\n\n## Example\n\n**Input:**\n\n```css\n.component {\n  margin: 16px;\n  padding: 8px 12px;\n  font-size: 1rem;\n}\n```\n\n**Output:**\n\n```css\n.component {\n  margin: calc(var(--spacing) * 4);\n  padding: calc(var(--spacing) * 2) calc(var(--spacing) * 3);\n  font-size: calc(var(--spacing) * 4);\n}\n```\n\n**Required CSS:**\n\n```css\n:root {\n  --spacing: 4px; /* Base unit */\n}\n```\n\n## Options\n\n```javascript\n// postcss.config.js\nimport tailwindPostcssSpacing from 'tailwind-postcss-spacing'\n\nexport default {\n  plugins: [\n    tailwindPostcssSpacing({\n      base: 4,                    // Base unit in px (default: 4)\n      remBase: 16,                // How many px in 1rem (default: 16)\n      varName: '--spacing',       // CSS variable name\n      preserveHairline: true,     // Keep borders ‚â§1px unchanged\n      ignoreProperties: []        // Properties to ignore\n    })\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n### CommonJS Usage\n\n```javascript\n// postcss.config.cjs\nconst tailwindPostcssSpacing = require(\"tailwind-postcss-spacing\");\n\nmodule.exports = {\n  plugins: [\n    tailwindPostcssSpacing({\n      base: 4,\n      varName: \"--spacing\",\n    }),\n  ],\n};\n\n## License\n\nMIT\n",
